Yemen President Saleh Names New Cabinet Ministers, Saba Says

-- B y   V i v i a n   S a l a m a
-- 
2011-03-14T06:52:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/yemen-president-saleh-names-new-cabinet-ministers-saba-says.html
Yemen’s President Ali Abdullah Saleh has announced changes to the government of Prime Minister
Ali Mohammed Mujawar, state-run Saba News Agency  reported .  According to the presidential decree, Hamoud Mohammad Abad
was named Minister of Endowments and Guidance and Aref Awad al-
Zoka has become Youth and Sports Minister, the report said.  Yemeni opposition movements have been holding daily
protests demanding Saleh’s departure for the past month.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vivian Salama in  Abu Dhabi  at  vsalama@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at  barden@bloomberg.net . 